e ID rather than positional indices."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"tip","name":"Tip"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"forEach","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features. It"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"runs the child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"possible for the parent feature to remove the child state from the array, in which case the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"child feature would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is still possible for a parent feature higher up in the application to remove the child"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state from the array before the child has a chance to react to the action. In such cases a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"runtime warning is shown in Xcode to let you know that there’s a potential problem.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/swift\/optional\/foreach(_:action:element:fileid:filepath:line:column:)-1dkh7"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Swift\/Optional\/forEach(_:action:element:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-1dkh7","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:22ComposableArchitecture7ReducerPAAE7forEach_6action7element6fileID0H4Path4line6columnQrs011WritableKeyJ0Cy5StateQz21IdentifiedCollections0P5ArrayVyqd_1_qd__GG_s0nJ0Cy9CasePaths0S0Vy6ActionQzGAXyAA0pU0Oyqd_1_qd_0_GGGqd_2_yXEs12StaticStringVA6_S2utAMQyd_2_Rsd__AYQyd_2_Rsd_0_SHRd_1_s8SendableRd_1_AaBRd_2_r2_lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:Sq","role":"symbol","symbolK